text: Grace Marie Stanke (born April 30, 2002) is an American pro-nuclear energy activist and beauty pageant contestant. She won Miss America in 2023. She was born in Wausau, Wisconsin. She is the third Miss Wisconsin to win the national title. After winning Miss America, Stanke earned a bachelor's degree in Nuclear Engineering in 2023 from the University of Wisconsin - Madison and began working at Constellation Energy, where she is an advocate for using nuclear energy. ==References== Category:2002 births Category:Living people Category:Miss America winners Category:American engineers Category:American activists Category:People from Wausau, Wisconsin
